# ║                   _m.sin() after CR2-PERF-7 removed those aliases but    ║
# ║                   missed these 4 call sites. NameError crashed the        ║
# ║                   Best Diff pulse animation 300 ms after launch.          ║
# ║                   Fixed: all 4 replaced with time.time() / math.*        ║
# ║ BUG-FIX-4 MED  — CONNECTION LOST overlay flickered over the hashrate    ║
# ║                   graph every 200 ms. Root cause: _draw_bars() called    ║
# ║                   c.delete("all") unconditionally before checking        ║
# ║                   offline state, causing a blank-then-redraw flash on    ║
# ║                   every animation tick. Fixed: overlay state evaluated   ║
# ║                   BEFORE any canvas clear; if state unchanged the        ║
# ║                   canvas is untouched and only the after() reschedule    ║
# ║                   fires. Overlay drawn exactly once on state transition.  ║
# ║ ── v5.4.0 patch-set (CR7 bug & perf audit — Selene) ──────────────────── ║
# ║ CR7-BUG-1 HIGH  — SettingsWindow._do_reboot called requests.post(timeout=5)  ║
# ║                    on the main Tk thread. UI froze for up to 5 s on every    ║
# ║                    reboot command. CR5-BUG-3 fixed _reboot_miner() in v5.2.10║
# ║                    but the SettingsWindow path was missed. Fixed: dash state  ║
# ║                    flags (_reboot_pending, stop_live/gold_pulse, offline_count║
# ║                    =0) set synchronously on UI thread; requests.post moved to ║
# ║                    daemon thread; success/error callbacks marshalled back via  ║
# ║                    self.after(0, ...).                                        ║
# ║ CR7-PERF-1 LOW   — numpy imported inside _remove_white_bg on every call.     ║
# ║                    Python caches module imports but the per-call dict lookup  ║
# ║                    adds noise and hides missing-numpy errors. Moved to        ║
# ║                    module-level try/except (guarded by _NUMPY_OK flag).       ║
# ║                    _remove_white_bg now raises ImportError immediately if     ║
# ║                    numpy is absent rather than failing silently mid-function. ║
# ║ CR7-PERF-2 MED   — _draw_gauge() called 5 times per update_display() tick    ║
# ║                    regardless of value change (4 fps default = 20 full canvas ║
# ║                    redraws/sec for gauges that haven't moved). Added per-     ║
# ║                    canvas value cache (_gauge_cache dict keyed by id(canvas));║
# ║                    skip redraw when |new − cached| < 0.3 AND value < crit.   ║
# ║                    Critical-zone always redraws so flash/colour change fires  ║
# ║                    on-time. Reduces gauge draw calls by ~80 % at steady-state.║
# ║ ── v5.4.2 patch-set (bad-share arrow — symmetric delta hysteresis) ────── ║
# ║ v5.4.2 DESIGN — Bad-share arrow is a momentum indicator with symmetric    ║
# ║                    0.03 pp hysteresis band (user-confirmed):               ║
# ║                    RED  (UP)   = rejection % rose   >= 0.03 pp from ref.  ║
# ║                    GREEN (DOWN) = rejection % fell   >= 0.03 pp from ref. ║
# ║                    Reference point locks at the pct value of each flip.   ║
# ║                    Both thresholds are symmetric — same 0.03 pp band in   ║
# ║                    each direction. Arrow reacts to rate-of-change, not    ║
# ║                    just presence of bad shares.                           ║
